This paper focuses on social networks and user behavior, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses visualization techniques for presenting user data, which could fall under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) or cybernetics (cs.CY). The use of recommended tweets based on user views and sensitive issues could also fall under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR) or computational linguistics (cs.CL).
